%h4 Privacy Policy

%p
  Harley Street Skin Care / 48 Harley Street (we) are committed
  to protecting and respecting your privacy.
  %br
  %br
  This policy sets out the basis on which any personal data we
  collect from you, or that you provide to us, will be
  processed by us. Please read the following carefully to
  understand our views and practices regarding your personal
  data and how we will treat it. By using our site and our
  services and by continuing to do so, you indicate your
  agreement to our use of your personal data as set out in this
  privacy policy.
  %br
  %br
  The date on which this Privacy Policy was first published is 28 February 2012.

%h4 The Data Controller

%p
  For the purpose of the Data Protection Act 1998 (the Act), the data
  controller is Harley Street Skin Care with our main trading address is 48
  Harley Street London, W1G 9PU.

%h4 Scope of this Privacy Policy

%p
  This Privacy Policy only applies to how we deal with your personal
  information, both the information which you knowingly chose to disclose to us
  and other information we collect from you as you interact with our site.
  %br
  %br
  This Policy does not apply to any other company or to any other company's
  websites even if you access them through our site. If you disclose your
  personal information to other companies your information will be dealt with
  according to their privacy policies and practices. We accept no
  responsibility or liability for other companies' sites.

%h4 Information We Collect From You

%p
  We may collect and process the following data about you:
  %br
  %br
  (a) Information that you provide by filling in forms on our site www.48harleystreetmembers.com (our site). This includes information provided at the time of registering as a member of our online club, subscribing to and using our services, posting materials or requesting further services.
  %br
  %br
  (b) If you contact us, whether by email, post, fax or telephone, or if we contact you, similarly we may keep a record of that correspondence.
  %br
  %br
  (c) We may also ask you to complete surveys that we use for research purposes, although you do not have to respond to them.
  %br
  %br
  (d) Details of transactions you carry out through our site.
  %br
  %br
  (e) Details of your visits to our site including, but not limited to, traffic data, location data, weblogs and other communication data, whether this is required for our own billing purposes or otherwise and the resources that you access.
  %br
  %br
  (f) If you enter into any of our competitions or promotions, we may ask for information about you, which will be made clear at the time you enter. We will also inform you of the purposes for which the information you provide may be used.
  %br
  %br
  (g) We collect information in aggregated form from users of our websites to help us to make improvements to the websites and to the services we make available. We know, for instance, how many visitors there are to each website, when they visited, for how long and to which areas of our website they went. We may share this information with our advertisers and to other companies which offer their goods or services on our websites. It helps to show these organisations how effective our websites are as sales channels for their products. However you or any other individual cannot be identified from the information we share as the data is aggregated and anonymous.

%h4 What Information is Published on the Site?

%p
  When you create your member profile (Profile) your name and email address and
  any other information you have chosen to make public will be available to
  other members and when you upload personal information in connection with
  your use of the site and our interactive services you will be making that
  personal information publicly available to all other members and guests of
  our online club and you do so at your own risk. If you do not wish to make
  certain information publicly available via your profile you should select the
  'private' option.
  %br
  %br
  Your name, email address and the name of any company or organisation you work
  for will be available to other members.
  %br
  %br
  Although we implement security measures in the site and we limit access to
  the site by third party search engine 'crawlers' but please do be aware that
  no security measures are perfect or impenetrable. Therefore, we cannot and do
  not guarantee that the personal information content you post on the site will
  not be viewed by unauthorised persons. Even after removal, copies of personal
  information you have chosen to upload to the site may have been copied and
  stored by other persons.
  %br
  %br
  We therefore urge you to consider carefully what information you upload to
  the site.
  %br
  %br
  Any improper collection or misuse of information is a breach of the website
  use agreement, and the acceptable use policy and should be reported to
  enquiries@48harleystreetmembers.com
  %br
  %br
  Once this information is made available on the site we will not be
  responsible for any use which is made of this information. If you do not want
  to make this information public you should not include it within your Profile
  or you should not use the interactive services.

%h4 IP Addresses and Cookies

%p
  We may collect information about your computer, including where available
  your IP address, operating system and browser type, for system administration
  and to report aggregate information to our advertisers. This is statistical
  data about our users' browsing actions and patterns, and does not identify
  any individual.
  %br
  %br
  For the same reason, we may obtain information about your general internet
  usage by using a cookie file which is stored on the hard drive of your
  computer. Cookies contain information that is transferred to your computer's
  hard drive. They help us to improve our site and to deliver a better and more
  personalised service. They enable us:
  %br
  %br
  (a) To estimate our audience size and usage pattern.
  %br
  %br
  (b) To store information about your preferences, and so allow us to customise
  our site according to your individual interests.
  %br
  %br
  (c) To speed up your searches.
  %br
  %br
  (d) To recognise you when you return to our site.
  %br
  %br
  You may refuse to accept cookies by activating the setting on your browser
  which allows you to refuse the setting of cookies. However, if you select
  this setting you may be unable to access certain parts of our site. Unless
  you have adjusted your browser setting so that it will refuse cookies, our
  system will issue cookies when you log on to our site.
  %br
  %br
  Please note that our advertisers may also use cookies, over which we have no
  control.

%h4 Where we Store Your Personal Data

%p
  The data that we collect from you may be transferred to, and stored at, a
  destination outside the European Economic Area ("EEA"). It may also be
  processed by staff operating outside the EEA who work for us or for one of
  our suppliers. Such staff maybe engaged in, among other things, the
  fulfilment of your order, the processing of your payment details and the
  provision of support services. By submitting your personal data, you agree to
  this transfer, storing or processing. We will take all steps reasonably
  necessary to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with
  this Privacy Policy.
  %br
  %br
  All information you provide to us is stored on our secure servers. Any
  payment transactions will be encrypted.
  %br
  %br
  Where we have given you (or where you have chosen) a password which enables
  you to access certain parts of our site, you are responsible for keeping this
  password confidential. We ask you not to share a password with anyone.
  %br
  %br
  Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the internet is not
  completely secure. Although we will do our best to protect your personal
  data, we cannot guarantee the security of your data transmitted to our site;
  any transmission is at your own risk.

%h4 Uses Made of the Information

%p
  We use information held about you in the following ways:
  %br
  %br
  (a) To ensure that content from our site is presented in the most effective
  manner for you and for your computer.
  %br
  %br
  (b) To help us to operate the site efficiently.
  %br
  %br
  (c) To provide you with information, products or services that you request
  from us.
  %br
  %br
  (d) To carry out our obligations arising from any contracts entered into
  between you and us.
  %br
  %br
  (e) To allow you to participate in interactive service, when you choose to do
  so.
  %br
  %br
  (f) To notify you about changes to our service.
  %br
  %br
  (g) To make operational communications to you.
  %br
  %br
  (h) To make service-related communications to you.
  %br
  %br
  (i) To communicate with you in relationship to your application to become a
  member of our online club or about your membership of our online club.
  %br
  %br
  If you do not wish to receive the communications referred to above please
  notify us at enquiries@48harleystreetmembers.com
  %br
  %br
  We may also use your data, to provide you with information about events,
  goods and services we offer which we believe may be of interest to you and we
  may contact you about these by post, telephone, SMS, email or fax for these
  purposes.
  %br
  %br
  We will not, other than as set out in this Privacy Policy, pass on your data
  or permit third parties to use your data.
  %br
  %br
  If you do not want us to use your data in this way, please tick the relevant
  box situated on the form on which we collect your data (the registration
  form).
  %br
  %br
  We do not disclose information about identifiable individuals to our
  advertisers, but we may provide them with aggregate information about our
  users (for example, we may inform them that 500 men aged under 30 have
  clicked on their advertisement on any given day). We may also use such
  aggregate information to help advertisers reach the kind of audience they
  want to target (for example, graphic designers in W1). We may make use of the
  personal data we have collected from you to enable us to comply with our
  advertisers' wishes by displaying their advertisement to that target
  audience.

%h4 Disclosure of Your Information

%p
  We may disclose your personal information to any member of our group, which
  means our subsidiaries, our ultimate holding company and its subsidiaries, as
  defined in section 736 of the UK Companies Act 1985.
  %br
  %br
  We may disclose your personal information to third parties:
  %br
  %br
  (a) To our group companies and to those suppliers to whom disclosure is
  necessary for the operation of our site or any of the services. Please note
  that we require any third party suppliers to process and store your data
  securely and they are prohibited from using it for any other purpose.
  %br
  %br
  (b) In the event that we sell or buy any business or assets, in which case we
  may disclose your personal data to the prospective seller or buyer of such
  business or assets.
  %br
  %br
  (c) If Harley Street Skin Care or substantially all of its assets are
  acquired by a third party, in which case personal data held by it about its
  customers will be one of the transferred assets.
  %br
  %br
  (d) If we are under a duty to disclose or share your personal data in order
  to comply with any legal obligation, or in order to enforce or apply the
  website use agreement and other agreements; or to protect the rights,
  property, or safety of Harley Street Skin Care, our members, our guests, or
  others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and
  organisations for the purposes of fraud protection and credit risk reduction.

%h4 Your Rights

%p
  You have the right to ask us not to process your personal data for marketing
  purposes. We will usually inform you (before collecting your data) if we
  intend to use your data for such purposes or if we intend to disclose your
  information to any third party for such purposes. You can exercise your right
  to prevent such processing by checking certain boxes on the forms we use to
  collect your data. You can also exercise the right at any time by contacting
  us at Data Registrar, Harley Street Skin Care, 48 Harley Street, London W1G
  9PU.
  %br
  %br
  Our website may, from time to time, contain links to and from the websites of
  our partner networks, advertisers and affiliates. If you follow a link to any
  of these websites, please note that these websites have their own privacy
  policies and that we do not accept any responsibility or liability for these
  policies. Please check these policies before you submit any personal data to
  these websites.

%h4 Access to Information

%p
  The Act gives you the right to access information held about you. Your right
  of access can be exercised in accordance with the Act. Any access request may
  be subject to a fee of £10 to meet our costs in providing you with details of
  the information we hold about you.
  %br
  %br
  How to access and update your email preferences, personal information and
  public information.
  %br
  %br
  You have the opportunity to opt-out of certain communications and to modify
  the non-public personal information you or the public information in your
  Profile at any time by going to the 'My Account' or 'My Profile' section of
  the site. Please be aware that it may take several hours for the change you
  make to take effect in the public areas of the website. Please note that any
  changes will only change or delete data in our database for the purposes of
  future activities and communications.

%h4 Changes to our Privacy Policy

%p
  Any changes we may make to our Privacy Policy in the future will be posted on
  this page and, where appropriate, notified to you by e-mail.
  %br
  %br
  Questions, comments and requests regarding this Privacy Policy are welcomed
  and should be addressed to the Data Registrar, Harley Street Skin Care, 48
  Harley Street, London W1G 9PU.

